description: [Beetroot, Parsnip & Carrot Crisps with a Pinch of Sea Salt, English Eccentrics, Whether it's the great uncle who organised dinner parties for dogs, or the grandmother who lived in an underground mansion filled with wigs   we love an English eccentric. Do you have a friend or relative with habits that are, how shall we say, a little unconventional? If so, regale us with a story about them and if it's suitably gigglesome, we'll publish it on our fully digital internet site and furnish you with some freebies. Just saunter over to www.tyrrellscrisps.co.uk/eccentrics, For the chance to win one of 100 cases of our crisps every month, just sign up to become an Official Taste Tester on our internet website thingy:, www.tyrrellscrisps.co.uk, The Tyrrells Alternative Five A Day, Steamed broccoli, herbal tea, sit ups: nothing terribly wrong with any of those (in moderation). But there is such a thing as taking it too far, you know., Which is why we came up with our own lifestyle guide, an alternative five a day. It's a simple list of things to keep your spirits up. Well, it works for us, A toasted tea cake, A snifter of port, A spot of sherry trifle, A game of Scrabble, A whole bag of English veg crisps, Tell us your alternative five a day at www.tyrrellscrisps.co.uk and if we love it we'll pop it on our website and give you a little pressie.]
